Key Match Events: Travis d'Arnaud hit a walk-off home run in the 9th inning
Post-Match Reflections: The Braves now lead both the Mets and D-backs by 1 game in the NL Wild Card race
The Braves can clinch a postseason berth with a win over the Royals on Sunday or a D-backs loss to the Padres
Miscellaneous Highlights: Reynaldo López returned to the mound and pitched 6 innings, allowing 2 hits and 1 run while striking out 9 batters
López's fastball reached 98.9 mph in the sixth inning
Charlie Morton will start the finale against the Royals on Sunday
